name: Suho
dialog: Dung-dung! P_name, hey! What brings you here today?
비고: (꽃에 물을 주며 정원을 가꾸고 있던 이장)

name: 주인공
dialog: I have something I want to ask the problem solver.

name: Suho
dialog: Of course, go ahead and tell me. I'll help you solve your problem today.
비고: (하던 일을 마무리 하듯 손을 탁탁 털며) (앉을 만한 곳으로 안내하며)

name: 주인공
dialog: I don't know what kind of dream I should have.

name: Suho
dialog: P_name! Before you think about what kind of dream to have, you should first think about what values you want to live by.

name: 주인공
dialog: Values? What do you mean by that?

name: Suho
dialog: Values mean what you think is important to yourself.

name: Suho
dialog: I think it's important to care for nature and neighbors.

name: Suho
dialog: What do you think is important, P_name?

name: 주인공
dialog: I'm not sure. I haven't thought about it.

name: Suho
dialog: Then it's time to draw some cards! Pick the things that you think are important among the 20 cards.

비고: 게임 화면이 나온다. 20개의 가치관이 써있는 표가 등장한다. 20개->10개->5개 5개는 중요 순서대로, (기차이미지)

name: Suho
dialog: By looking at the cards you've chosen, you can see what P_name thinks is important.

name: Suho
dialog: These values will help you achieve your dreams.

name: Suho
dialog: And if you try to find something you like and are good at, you will eventually achieve your dream.
